# JS lifecycle

**Acyclic:** Before wiring classes, stop and ask if ownership, init/start order, or dispose would cycle (A↔B, init needs start loop). No silent cycles.

**Phases:**
- `constructor` — alloc only: fields, `new Child()`; no DOM/GL/listeners/I/O
- `init()` — memory, refs, child `init()`; no operational side effects
- `start()` — purpose work (listen, hook, run)
- `stop()` — reverse `start()` plus end all lifetime ops (`step()`, timers, ticks, in-flight state); idempotent
- `dispose()` — `stop()` if needed, reverse `init()`, null refs, child `dispose()`

**Composite:** parent drives phase; unwind children in reverse order.

**Violations:** ctor side effects, alloc in `start()` without `stop()` cleanup, parent↔child cycles → stop and ask.
